# Chimney Inspection App

A React Native mobile application for conducting and documenting chimney inspections.

## Project Structure
/chimney-inspection-app
├── App.js
├── package.json
├── /src
│ ├── /components
│ │ ├── PhotoCapture.js
│ │ └── AttentionItems.js
│ ├── /screens
│ │ ├── HomeScreen.js
│ │ ├── InspectionTypeScreen.js
│ │ ├── TraditionalMasonryInterior.js
│ │ ├── TraditionalMasonryExterior.js
│ │ ├── PrefabricatedInterior.js
│ │ ├── PrefabricatedExterior.js
│ │ └── ReportScreen.js
│ ├── /utils
│ │ ├── attentionTriggers.js
│ │ └── constants.js
│ └── /styles
│ └── globalStyles.js


## Installation

```bash
# Create new React Native project
npx react-native init ChimneyInspectionApp

# Navigate to project directory
cd ChimneyInspectionApp

# Install dependencies
npm install @react-navigation/native @react-navigation/stack
npm install react-native-elements
npm install expo-image-picker
npm install expo-print
npm install expo-sharing
npm install react-native-safe-area-context
npm install react-native-screens
npm install @react-native-masked-view/masked-view
npm install react-native-gesture-handler
Key Features
Traditional Masonry Fireplace Inspection
Interior inspection
Exterior inspection
Prefabricated Fireplace Inspection
Interior inspection
Chase exterior inspection
Photo capture and documentation
Automated attention items based on inspection findings
PDF report generation with photos
Report sharing capabilities
Development Notes
The app uses React Native Elements for UI components
Photo capture uses Expo Image Picker
PDF generation uses Expo Print
Navigation uses React Navigation v6
All forms include photo capture capabilities
Attention triggers are centralized in utils/attentionTriggers.js
